(Description)
Given the head of a linked list and an integer val, remove all the nodes of the linked list that has Node.val == val, and return the new head.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public ListNode removeElements(ListNode head, int val) {
        while (head != null && head.val == val) {
            head = head.next;
        }

        ListNode cover = head;

        while (cover != null && cover.next != null) {
            if (cover.next.val == val) {
                cover.next = cover.next.next;
            } else {
                cover = cover.next;
            }
        }

        return head;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
There were two while loops.

1. First one is for setting the right beginning point.
If the head itself have the val which is same with given int val, it must set find another next node, having diffeent val with given one.

2. The second loop is for covering from first to the last to eliminate nodes that have val same with given val.
Using the if statement, when the next node's val is same with given val, it eliminate the next node,
else it made the pointer forward.
